title: Contributing to GeoPressureR
text: Fork package clone onto computer. haven’t done , recommend using usethis::create_from_github("Rafnuss/GeoPressureR", fork = TRUE). Install development dependencies devtools::install_dev_deps(), make sure package passes R CMD check running devtools::check(). R CMD check doesn’t pass cleanly, ’s good idea ask help continuing. Create Git branch pull request (PR). recommend using usethis::pr_init("brief-description--change"). Make changes, commit git, create PR running usethis::pr_push(), following prompts browser. title PR briefly describe change. body PR contain Fixes #issue-number. user-facing changes, add bullet top NEWS.md (.e. just first header). Follow style described https://style.tidyverse.org/news.html.

title: Compute likelihood map from pressure data — geopressure_map
text: geopressure_map_mismatch() computes mismatch maps Google Earth Engine via map entry point GeoPressure API. consists following steps: Pre-process pressure: pressure measurements first smoothed downscaled 1-hour resolution order match ERA-5 resolution (see geopressure_map_preprocess()). Generate requests: Send single request GeoPressureAPI generate Google Earth Engine (GEE) URLs, one elevation/stationary period can used compute maps GEE server. Send requests: Call URLs, start computation GEE server. step, wait answer, send requests parallel faster. Compute download maps: requests sent, wait GEE server return geotiff file (map) elevation/ stationary period. Post-process maps: Read geotiff maps matrix, create corresponding GeoPressureR map object create_map(). following two maps returned stationary period: map_pressure_mse: Mean Square Error (MSE) data logger pressure timeseries reanalysis. mean error removed assume specific altitude geolocator, thus allowing altitudinal shift pressure timeseries. map_pressure_mask (optionally): mask proportion pressure measurements corresponding altitude values found within min max ground elevation location. altitude value geolocator pressure timeseries computed barometric formula accounting temporal variation pressure (surface-pressure) temperature (2m-temperature) based ERA5 data. min max ground elevation pixel computed SRTM-90. map returned keep_mask TRUE. details, read GeoPressure API documentation .

what: Convert mismatch map into likelihood map
title: Compute likelihood map from pressure data — geopressure_map
text: convert map mean square error \(MSE\) altitude mask \(z_{mask}\) computed geopressure_map_mismatch() likelihood map , $$L = \left( \frac{1}{2 \pi \sigma^2}\right)^{\frac{nw}{2}} \exp \left(-w n \frac{MSE}{2\sigma^2} \right) \left[z_{mask}>T \right],$$ \(\sigma\) standard deviation (sd) pressure \(T\) mask threshold (thr_mask). auto-correlation timeseries accounted equation, use log-linear pooling weight \(w=\log(n)/n\) default, \(n\) number samples timeserie (.e., data points used compute MSE). See GeoPressureManual | Probability aggregation  details. Important Note: Since GeoPressure v3.1.0, threshold mask happening directly GEE server (.e., geopressure_map_mismatch()). allows compute MSE pixels within threshold, thus reducing computational cost significantly.

what: Request and download pressure timeseries at a given location — geopressure_timeseries
title: Request and download pressure timeseries at a given location — geopressure_timeseries
text: function returns surface atmospheric pressure timeseries ERA5 requested location. location queried water, location moved closest onshore location. ERA5 pressure timeseries response \(P_{ERA}\) provided hourly basis start_time end_time pressure$date pressure supplied. supply pressure geolocator \(P_{gl}\), function additionally return altitude geolocator sea level \(z_{gl}\) using barometric equation, $$ z_{{gl}}(x)=z_{ERA5}(x) + \frac{T_{ERA5}(x)}{L_b}  \left( \frac{P_{gl}}{P_{ERA5}(x)} \right)^{\frac{RL_b}{g M}-1},$$ \(z_{ERA}\), \(T_{ERA}\), \(P_{ERA}\) respectively correspond ground level elevation, temperature 2m, ground level pressure ERA5, \(L_b\)  standard temperature lapse rate, \(R\) universal gas constant, \(g\) gravity constant  \(M\) molar mass air. See information GeoPressureAPI documentation. able compare temporal variation retrieved pressure ERA5 \(P_{ERA}\) geolocator pressure \(P_{gl}\), function also returns ERA pressure normalized geolocator mean pressure measurement pressure_era5_norm. $$ P_{ERA5,0}(\boldsymbol{x})[t] = \left( P_{ERA5}(\boldsymbol{x})[t]-P_{gl}[t]\right) - \left( \frac{1}{n}\sum_{=1}^{n} P_{ERA5}(\boldsymbol{x})[]-P_{gl}[] \right).$$

title: Create a tag object — tag_create
text: Create GeoPressureR tag object data collected tracking device. data needs include least pressure optionally light /acceleration. current implementation can read files following three manufacturer: Swiss Ornithological Institute (soi) pressure_file = "*.pressure" light_file = "*.glf" (optional) acceleration_file = "*.acceleration" (optional) Migrate Technology (migratetech): pressure_file = "*.deg" light_file = "*.lux" (optional) acceleration_file = "*.deg" (optional) Lund CAnMove (lund) pressure_file = "*_press.xlsx" light_file = "*_acc.xlsx" (optional) acceleration_file = "*_acc.xlsx" (optional) can also enter data manually (manufacturer = "manual") providing data.frame pressure_file: pressure_file: data.frame column date value. light_file: (optional) data.frame column date value. acceleration_file: (optional) data.frame column date value. default manufacturer = NULL, manufacturer determined automatically content directory. can also specify manually file full pathname file extension using regex expression (e.g., "*.pressure" matches file ending pressure). what: Configure the map of a tag object — tag_set_map
title: Configure the map of a tag object — tag_set_map
text: function adds tag parameters defining 3D grid map. spatial parameters (extent scale) define geographical dimensions map, temporal dimension defined based stationary periods built using labels. include_stap_id include_min_duration can used limit stationary periods computed modelled analysis. default, stationary periods included. addition, tag offers possibility define known locations (e.g., equipment retrieval site). can defined level stationary period (.e., assuming constant position whole stationary period) can define many known stationary periods wish. default (see compute_known geopressure_map()), likelihood map computed stationary periods trajectory model constrained, saving significant computational time. index last stationary period generally unknown, can use negative indexing known, .e., known$stap_id = -1 converted nrow(tag$stap).

title: Configure the map of a tag object — tag_set_map
code: tag_set_map(   tag,   extent,   scale = 10,   known = data.frame(stap_id = integer(), known_lat = double(), known_lon = double()),   include_stap_id = tag$stap$stap_id,   include_min_duration = 0 )

title: Configure the map of a tag object — tag_set_map
text: tag GeoPressureR tag object. extent geographical extent map likelihood graph model computed. Vector length 4 c(xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax) c(W, E, S, N). scale number pixels per 1° latitude-longitude. instance, scale = 10 resolution 0.1° (~10km) scale=4 resolution 0.25° (~30km). avoid interpolating ERA5 data, scale equal smaller 10. Read scale Google earth Engine documentation . known data.frame containing known positions bird (e.g., equipment retrieval site) columns stap_id, known_lat known_lon. can set position last stationary period using stap_id = -1. include_stap_id vector stap_id defining stationary period model, , compute likelihood map use graph. include_min_duration minimum duration threshold stationary periods include (hours).

title: Configure the map of a tag object — tag_set_map
text: GeoPressureR tag object : stap: Data.frame stationary periods three new columns: known_lat known_lon define known position stationary periods, model defines whether likelihood map stationary period computed later used graph. extent input parameter extent scale input parameter scale
